text: Anna Linnea Södahl, better known as Nea (born 17 September 1986) is a Swedish singer and songwriter. Nea was born in South Africa, where her parents were working against the apartheid system, she later grew up in Alingsås, Sweden. As a songwriter, Nea has written songs for singers like Zara Larsson, Tove Styrke, Tinie Tempah and Axwell. Her songs have so far received over a billion streams on Spotify. On 22 December 2019, Nea was placed number one as a singer and number three as a songwriter on Svensktoppen with the songs "Some Say" (which interpolates Eiffel 65's "Blue (Da Ba Dee)") and "Fira jul med mig" (performed by Linnea Henriksson). ==Discography== ===Extended plays=== {| class="wikitable plainrowheaders" style="text-align:center;" |- ! scope="col" rowspan="2"| Title ! scope="col" rowspan="2"| Year ! scope="col" colspan="2"| Peak chart positions |- ! scope="col" style="width:2.5em;font-size:90%;"| SWE ! scope="col" style="width:2.5em;font-size:90%;"| NOR |- ! scope="row"| Some Say - EP | 2020 | — || — |} ===Singles=== {| class="wikitable plainrowheaders" style="text-align:center;" |- ! scope="col" rowspan="2"| Title ! scope="col" rowspan="2"| Year ! scope="col" colspan="4"| Peak chart positions ! scope="col" rowspan="2"| Album |- ! scope="col" style="width:2.5em;font- size:90%;"| SWE ! scope="col" style="width:2.5em;font-size:90%;"| NOR ! scope="col" style="width:2.5em;font-size:90%;"| AUS ! scope="col" style="width:2.5em;font-size:90%;"|SK |- ! scope="row"| "Some Say" | 2019 | 12 || 6 || 13 || 1 | |- ! scope="row"| "TG4M" | rowspan="3" |2020 |86 |— |— |— | rowspan="3" |- ! scope="row"| "No Therapy" |— |— |67 |— |- ! scope="row"| "Diablo" (with Nio Garcia) |— |— |— |— |} ==References== Category:Swedish female singers Category:1986 births Category:Living people Category:South African people of Swedish descent Category:South African expatriates in Sweden Category:Swedish expatriates in South Africa Category:Swedish people of South African descent
